Ielts topic: In many countries there are people with extremely high incomes Some say it is good for the country while others claim that governments should limit salaries Discuss both views and give your opinion The rain-storm development of society brings along the standing risks of our unstable day-to-day lives In which a standardised basic salary is one of the most brain-cracking issue While some claim that it is vital for a country to have many people of property others support the government in an effort to grind to a halt of the richโ income My essay will look at both sides of this matter through objective eyes Admittedly personal income from financial activities claims a big share to the development of a country Conventional wisdom has it that if there are more and more wealthy people participating in the social innovation task their nations could be enriched to a certain extent As a recent survey from the center for social research and community development publicity and the national economy enjoy the sweetness of high and rich peopleโs contribution every year To be more specific a huge numerous personal tax coming from the rich flows into national budget is the premise for the highest standards of infrastructures health care and other social services Taking a closer look into the picture of the current society we can see a growing increase in fund raising events which are held by the people with extremely high incomes They come from different social classes from business men to politicians but they are getting on the right track charitably They are well-known for their selfless donations and their philanthropic deeds with out a profit-driven purpose If it were not for the appearance of few small illegally enriched groups the government would have no reason to manipulate the personal income To live a life of luxury and success a number of people dare to trample upon othersโ interests They are blindfolded by the wealth and it comes naturally that they put the national budget in jeopardy Thus it is high time for government to prepare the ground for freezing out these people All above analysis leads to the conclusion that limiting salaries of employees needs a cautious consideration and sanction in which to satisfy the whole society before taking it into effect

My third essay and the topic is: "Decreasing levels of fresh water sources are becoming a global issue What are the reasons? What can be done by governments to prevent it?" ( Newest Ielts writing test) The riverside โ with storks drying their wings in the sun fresh water fishes swimming freely near the banks and native hibiscus in bloom - is beautiful But its fragility is no longer visible covered by invasive algae and waste Riverside is not alone in its distress In the last 10 years many of the freshwater rivers reservoirs lakes and streams have seen a dramatically rise in the level of pollution Those of us are fortunate generally we do not have to give a lot of thought to the safety of our water This makes our understanding of water very different from that of hundreds of millions people across the globe who lack access to clean water It is believed that fresh water is becoming increasingly scarce in the future and this is partly due to a myriad of forces including climate change population blooming and over-development Environmental experts from many regions recently raise their anxiety that climate change is likely to increase water demand while shrinking water supplies As temperature rises people and animals need more water to maintain their health and thrive while they also have to share water with agriculture energy production navigation recreation and manufacturing These uses put pressure on water resources In the mean time fresh water reserves become limited with every passing day due to warmer temperature Investigation indicates that warming temperatures cause increased evaporation that dries out some areas consequently dry regions may face increasing water scarcity However the direct impact of climate change is not the only reason - a fact highlighted by a recent United Nations Environment Program report The population blooming and over-development have been two significant factors in rising global water consuming On occasion of urbanization economic development and improved living standards in 19th century for example has seen a water crisis in some water-scare countries where each person is only allowed to use less than 1 000 cubic meters per year That means they are living in danger of a great deal of illness caused by lacking of clean water Meanwhile in many parts enormous amounts of water are wasted due to inappropriate agricultural subsidies inefficient irrigation systems poor management and other practices Our environment particularly in fresh water is rapidly suffering The situation will be out of control if we ignore the weaknesses in our current approaches to protect our drinking water supplies It is needed to call for a change in using fresh water and as a matter of-course the water policies should be implemented properly by the local authorities Protecting fresh water is uneasy task and incessant progress The government have to be patient in the battle for keeping clean water in reserve The budget on water utilities should be put into priority and expanded Come along with this it is essential to establish a special office in each country to take main responsibility in managing drinking water It is expected that national government could do more to reduce our anxiety in the struggle against water scarcity

How should they be punished? While the authorities are sitting in a room to question each other that โhow has juvenile delinquency multiplied dramatically in our society?โ in the outsides one second gone one child was found committing crime Youth crimes nowadays is often regarded as a topic issue with โsky-is-fallingโ tongue and as a matter of course it needs an answer from social workers to come to a brighter future of no crime In stead of complaining and imputing blame to a typical person or typical organization letโs ourselves hand in hand to bring the teenage crimes back to life In the eyes of media all youngsters who commit crime should bear the scorn of society and must be punished under the national law Youth crimes - they are always known as the teenagers from hell and do not have rights in society I am often on this path of thought until I recognize the so-call โ the roots of crimeโ The teenager crimes have not always been like our prejudice and the paradox is that they are all miserable than our imagination There are a wide range of factors that account for adolescentsโ strong aggressive and criminal tendencies including poverty unstable family life violence delinquent peer groups and so forth But the question is that what are the main reasons that digs young criminals to the bottom A number of social investigations believe that unstable family life is considered as the first common factor responsible for juvenile crime The children who live with single-mother single-father or without parents often show their bad behaviors in society and are in high chance of committing crime They live with their thinking that they have nothing to lose and the majority of them has been easily abused by some groups of gangsters It must be the most thankless job when the children โ they always receive less than what they donate for the abusers Besides violence also have a big hand in bringing children to the criminal routes Violence comes from family from the dads and mums who maltreat the children from the Internet from video games from films and so forth At a court when being asked why commits murder ? a child answers with his cold face: โ I was thinking that my grandmother could be reborn after death as in a gameโ His innocent thought makes everyone in this court frozen in a moment The responsibility is of whom? And is he worth to bear the blame? The questions have no answers and perhaps tear is the concluding part of a tragic ending If I have a wish I wish that the children from all corners of the world could be treated equally Donโt forsake the youngsters when they have wrongdoing They were born humans so they have rights to live and be happy with this People can win wild beastโs heart much less than a small child as long as they live in cherishable arms they will be grown up from their mistakes Above all children should be received in an advanced education with positive orientation of life It can be sure that they have no reasons to commit the crime even for once

Thรnh quแบฃ sau 1 thรกng hแปc writing :) Topic: Women and men are commonly seen as having different strength and weaknesses Is it right to exclude males or females from certain professions because of their gender? Stepping in to the competitive world women have set their foot in every walk of life However in much of the world some areas are still male-dominated Are men impossibly holding their higher ascendancy above women? I believe that a great many people especially men hold the answers that โ it is obviously trueโ In my perceptions success is in the hands of those who dare to walk on the path of fire and thorn to claim their talents In other words gender equality should be widely promoted in todayโsociety both males and females can assume their responsibility for any professions The first point to note is that society does not assign either males or females to do a certain kind of job and gender discrimination is no longer valuable in comparision with the past Modern community treats us the same social conditions and the same advanced education That means we have more and full chances to develop ourselves in every area at highest level Thus the most skillful person will be appointed to an important post no matter whether they are males or females It is said that the 21st century marks an unmistakable progress in occupational segregation which has cracked many authoritiesโs brain Emerging as a typical example of the success Japanese government makes the best of reviving a crowded female workforce and promulgating the laws of openness in professions History predicates that Japanese women especially married have experienced a period of gender discrimination that they did not have any chances of promotion at work It is extremely unfair and it is the root of commotions in Japanese community Back up to the issue of occupational segregation perhaps from now on no politicians in any countries make the same mistake as Japanese ones in the past It is crystal clear that politicians value peaceful labor above riots Secondly no one has inborn merits that stand them in good stead Professions in the fields of mathematics computer science the natural sciences and technology are for men and not for women This attitude is far from being valid According to a newest study if a man finds himself working in a โfemale- orientedโ job he ends up earning 12 5 percent less than his male counterparts whereas a woman who works in a โmale-dominatedโ field earns 25 9 percent more than her female peers So interestingly women in fact are earning more than men because of their less committing faults and their capacity of dealing with matters with accuracy and caution Thus what is the best solution for the thorny problem of making a more equal workforce? There is no way around but the labor pool must be balanced out by drawing from a supply of trained men or women to cover the skill gaps But it is tough to achieve in reality if gender discrimination is alive Therefore it is time to exclude job stereotyping by gender from our community if we want to see men in the maternity ward and day care centers or women in trucking construction and heavy machinery operations It would be great to achieve an ideal employment balance on a national scale and we believe in the right direction of our government for a workforce that never sleeps

Nhแปฏng bฦฐแปc sau lร nhแปฏng bฦฐแปc cฦก bแบฃn ฤแป bแบกn cรณ thแป ngฤn ngแปซa vร trแป mแปฅn: a/ Rแปญa mแบทt nhแบน nhรng Nhiแปu ngฦฐแปi lแบงm tฦฐแปng rแบฑng bแปฅi bแบฉn lร nguyรชn nhรขn chรญnh gรขy nรชn mแปฅn nรชn rแปญa mแบทt quรก tay gรขy tแปn thฦฐฦกng cho da Nhแปฏng ngฦฐแปi da mแปฅn ngฦฐแปฃc lแบกi nรชn rแปญa mแบทt nhแบน nhรng 2 lแบงn mแปt ngรy ฤแป diแปt vi khuแบฉn vร rแปญa sแบกch dแบงu nรชn chแปn nhแปฏng loแบกi nฦฐแปc rแปญa mแบทt dแปu nhแบน ko chแปฉa cแปn vร khรดng gรขy khรด da ฤแป trรกnh da kรญch แปฉng b/ Tแบฉy da chแบฟt bแบฑng Salicylic Acid (loแบกi BHA thรดng dแปฅng nhแบฅt) cรณ tรกc dแปฅng tแบฉy da chแบฟt hoรก hแปc tแปt hฦกn nhiแปu tแบฉy da chแบฟt cฦก hแปc thรดng thฦฐแปng Salicylic Acid lร loแบกi acid khแบฃ nฤng hoร tan dแบงu (oil-soluble) cรณ thแป thแบฅm sรขu vรo tแบญn lแป chรขn lรดng Loแบกi acid nรy lร mแปt cรกch hแปฏu hiแปu ฤแป giแบฃi quyแบฟt cรกc vแบงn ฤแป cแปงa da mแปฅn c/ Sแปญ dแปฅng cรกc sแบฃn phแบฉm trแป mแปฅn ko cแบงn ฤฦกn Cรกc sแบฃn phแบฉm trแป mแปฅn bรกn ko cแบงn ฤฦกn (vรญ dแปฅ nhฦฐ drying lotion) thฦฐแปng chแปฉa cรกc chแบฅt benzoyl peroxide sulfur hoแบทc resorcinol Cรกc chแบฅt nรy cรณ tรกc dแปฅng khรกng khuแบฉn lรm khรด dแบงu trong mแปฅn Tuy nhiรชn cรกc sแบฃn phแบฉm nรy thฦฐแปng chแป cรณ tรกc dแปฅng trong vรฒng 1-2 thรกng ฤแบงu vร sau ฤรณ sแบฝ cรณ hiแปn tฦฐแปฃng โnhแปn thuแปcโ Chรญnh vรฌ thแบฟ khi sแปญ dแปฅng cรกc sแบฃn phแบฉm nรy nรชn kแบฟt hแปฃp vแปi 2 bฦฐแปc แป trรชn ฤแป triแปt tแบญn gแปc nguแปn cแปงa mแปฅn trรกnh tรฌnh trแบกng โnhแปn thuแปcโ vรฌ sau 2 thรกng mร mแปฅn mแปi vแบซn mแปc thรฌ cรกch nรy cลฉng bรณ tay

column5: ๐ก HYALURONIC ACID CแบคP แบจM CHO DA NHฦฏ THแบพ NรO ? ---------------------- ๐ข Hyaluronic Acid cรณ thแป giแปฏ 1 lฦฐแปฃng nฦฐแปc gแบฅp 1000 lแบงn khแปi lฦฐแปฃng cแปงa nรณ 1 gram Hyaluronic Acid cรณ thแป giแปฏ ฤฦฐแปฃc ฤแบฟn 6 lรญt nฦฐแปc ๐ข ๐ Sau khi thแบฉm thแบฅu xuแปng da Hyaluronic Acid sแบฝ biแบฟn lแปp dermis (hแบก bรฌ) cแปงa da thรnh mแปt miแบฟng mรบt cรณ khแบฃ nฤng hรบt vร giแปฏ nฦฐแปc cao ฤแปng thแปi giแบฃm thoรกt nฦฐแปc qua da ๐ Hyaluronic Acid hiแปn nay ฤรฃ ฤฦฐแปฃc sแปญ dแปฅng nhiแปu trong cรกc sแบฃn phแบฉm dฦฐแปกng da giรบp cแบฅp nฦฐแปc dฦฐแปกng แบฉm lรm da cฤng mแปn phแบงn nรo lรm ฤแบงy vร giแบฃm bแปt nhแปฏng nแบฟp nhฤn nhแป Ngoรi ra Hyaluronic Acid cรฒn thรบc ฤแบฉy quรก trรฌnh tแบกo ra collagen vร tแบฟ bรo mแปi ๐ Hyaluronic Acid ฤฦฐแปฃc xem lร an toรn รญt gรขy kรญch แปฉng phรน hแปฃp vแปi ฤa sแป nhiแปu loแบกi da lร thรnh phแบงn dฦฐแปกng แบฉm hiแปu quแบฃ dรnh cho da dแบงu da mแปฅn vร da thiแบฟu nฦฐแปc โ Lฦฐu รฝ khi sแปญ dแปฅng Hyaluronic Acid (HA) โช ฤแป tแปi ฦฐu hรณa hiแปu quแบฃ cแปงa cรกc sแบฃn phแบฉm chแปฉa HA แป nแปng ฤแป cao hay trรกnh hรบt แบฉm ngฦฐแปฃc tแปซ da bแบกn ฤแปซng bรดi trแปฑc tiแบฟp HA lรชn da trแบงn mร hรฃy sแปญ dแปฅng lแปp toner/lotion dฦฐแปกng แบฉm trฦฐแปc rแปi mแปi ฤแบฟn Hyaluronic Acid โช ฤแป แบฉm nฦกi bแบกn แป cลฉng phแบงn nรo quyแบฟt ฤแปnh hiแปu quแบฃ cแปงa Hyaluronic Acid trรชn da Tแบกi nฦกi khรญ hแบญu khรด ฤแป แบฉm thแบฅp hoแบทc lรm viแปc trong phรฒng mรกy lแบกnh nhiแปu giแป bแบกn cรณ thแป trang bแป thรชm mรกy phun sฦฐฦกng trong phรฒng ฤแป phรกt huy hiแปu quแบฃ cแปงa HA
